      "subtasks": [],
      "created": "2015-05-11T16:48:18.347+0000",
      "description": "The initial design called for the node manager to write YARN container events to take advantage of the distributed writes. RM acting as a sole writer of all YARN container events would have significant scalability problems.\n\nStill, there are some types of events that are not captured by the NM. The current implementation has both: RM writing container events and NM writing container events.\n\nWe need to sort this out, and decide how we can write all needed container events in a scalable manner.",
      "priority": {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/priority/3",
        "iconUrl": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg",
        "name": "Major",
        "id": "3"
      },
      "resolution": {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/resolution/2",
        "id": "2",
        "description": "The problem described is an issue which will never be fixed.",
        "name": "Won't Fix"
      },
